---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Character Creation"
  summary="Build a Ka-Tet character in six clear steps, then tie them to the party and the road ahead."
  eyebrow="Player creation"
  audience="player"
>
  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Six-Step Summary</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Choose a concept and world of origin.</li>
      <li>Pick an archetype that matches your play style.</li>
      <li>Assign ability scores to show strengths and weaknesses.</li>
      <li>Choose background, gear, and a first personal scar.</li>
      <li>Set derived stats, starting moves, and Ka.</li>
      <li>Write one bond to another member of the ka-tet.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="two-column">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Ability Scores</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Score</th>
            <th>Use It For</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Strength</td><td>Force, endurance, brutal leverage</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dexterity</td><td>Aim, reflex, stealth, balance</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Constitution</td><td>Survival, resilience, punishment</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Intelligence</td><td>Recall, analysis, relic logic</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Wisdom</td><td>Perception, instinct, reading the wrongness</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Charisma</td><td>Presence, command, song, conviction</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Starting Level Guidance</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Mode</th>
            <th>Recommended Level</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Intro Demo</td><td>3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Campaign Opening</td><td>1-3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Experienced Table</td><td>4-5</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        For the MVP site, level 3 is the sweet spot: enough signature identity to feel cool, not
        so much complexity that new players bog down.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Background Examples</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Background</th>
          <th>What It Suggests</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Road Medic</td><td>Healing under pressure, triage, grim calm</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Choir Runaway</td><td>Faith, music, fear of authority</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ruin Courier</td><td>Maps, doors, smuggling, bad instincts turned useful</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Failed Knight</td><td>Old vows, armor, unresolved duty</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Bond Questions</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Which member of the tet reminds you of someone you failed before?</li>
        <li>Whose survival feels non-negotiable to you?</li>
        <li>Who do you trust with your secret, and why?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Example Character</p>
      <p>
        Naomi Blueglass is a Singer from 1987 Harlem whose voice bends fear into stillness. Her
        bond says she hears the same unfinished melody in one other party member, and she refuses
        to let them face it alone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
